 2. License Notice for FFmpeg
-----------------------------------------------
This software uses FFmpeg, a free software project licensed under
the GNU Lesser General Public License (LGPL) version 2.1 or later,
or, if configured with --enable-gpl, the GNU General Public License (GPL) version 2.

The official FFmpeg source code is available at:
    https://github.com/FFmpeg/FFmpeg
    https://ffmpeg.org/

This distribution contains statically linked FFmpeg binaries.
Under the terms of the LGPL/GPL, the corresponding source code of the
FFmpeg version used to build these binaries may be obtained from:

    https://github.com/FFmpeg/FFmpeg

Alternatively, you may request the same FFmpeg source code from the author
for a period of three years from the date of this distribution.

-----------------------------------------------
 3. License Compatibility Notes
-----------------------------------------------
Because FFmpeg was statically linked into the VideoPlayer DLL:

- If FFmpeg was built **without** GPL components (LGPL mode):
      The VideoPlayer API Library may be distributed under LGPLv3 or GPLv3.
      Source code of this project is provided so that users may relink
      the library with a modified version of FFmpeg if desired.

- If FFmpeg was built **with** GPL components:
      The entire VideoPlayer API Library must be distributed under GPLv3.

